&lt;p&gt;GM Land Solutions were approached by a large company based in the Highlands, to undertake a slightly different job from normal.&amp;nbsp; The company own a part of Venlaw Forest in Peebles, and required a contractor to reinstate a very overgrown forestry road.&amp;nbsp; The difficulty they found before speaking to GM Land Solutions, was that although there were groundwork companies, there werent any they found that did the forestry part of it as well.&amp;nbsp; The problem was that there were trees grown up on the road, and overhanging branches needing cleared, therefore they needed a business with the relevent certification, insurance and expertese to do both tree surgery works and groundworks with a digger to then clear the vegiation and tree roots from the road.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GM Land soltions took on the job, initially 2200 Meters of road to do, but then on the manager seeing the job, it was extended by another 800 Meters as they were so pleased with the finished result.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see photos below.&amp;nbsp; The 7.5 Ton digger seen in the photo, recently purchased by Gavin, was perfect for this size of job.&lt;/p&gt;
